{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`typed-action-registry-keybindings` shipped canonical `prompt.transform.*` action IDs and opt-in `piVimMode.keymap.actions`. Current docs show raw examples, but users still need to know which transform IDs compose into useful workflows. Runtime help can find actions and bindings, but it does not yet surface recommended copy-paste recipes. This change is documentation/discovery-first. It should not change prompt transform semantics, modal dispatch, default keymaps, or the config schema beyond reu"}, {"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Make common prompt transform action keybindings easy to adopt with copy-pasteable settings recipes."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 25", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. **Represent recipes as source-backed metadata, not config behavior.** - Target seams: `src/runtime-help.ts`, possibly a small `src/action-keybinding-recipes.ts`, `test/docs-drift.test.ts`, `test/runtime-help.test.ts`, `docs/settings.md`, `docs/features.md`. - Decision: add curated recipe data that describes existing `piVimMode.keymap.actions` snippets. Recipes are examples only; resolving default options must still produce no accepted action bindings."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 52", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- **Runtime help output becomes too long** \u2192 Keep `:features keybindings` compact and put full formatted snippets in docs; include enough snippet text to be actionable. - **Recipe keys conflict with user custom mappings** \u2192 State recipes are examples and rely on existing validation/warnings; no defaults are installed. - **Docs snippets drift from source-backed recipe metadata** \u2192 Add drift tests that parse recipe configs and check docs anchors/action IDs/keys."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 60", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. Add source-backed recipe metadata or local runtime-help recipe helpers. 2. Update runtime feature/help output for keybinding recipe discovery. 3. Add docs snippets in settings/features docs with stable anchors."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_open_questions", "label": "Open Questions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 70", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Should recipe metadata live in a dedicated module (`src/action-keybinding-recipes.ts`) or stay inside `src/runtime-help.ts` until it grows? - Should `:features keybindings` show full one-line JSON snippets or only compact recipe summaries plus docs pointers? - Should the compact cleanup recipe ship in this change, or wait for user feedback after paragraph/Markdown recipes?"}, {"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_ref_src_runtime_help_ts", "label": "runtime-help.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 28", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_ref_src_action_keybinding_recipes_ts", "label": "action-keybinding-recipes.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 28", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_ref_test_docs_drift_test_ts", "label": "docs-drift.test.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 28", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_ref_test_runtime_help_test_ts", "label": "runtime-help.test.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 28", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_action_keybinding_presets_design_ref_docs_settings_md", "label": "settings.md", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-ac